x4freetext: 250 KEV ACCELERATOR OF THE INSTITUT FUER RADIUM-
A REACTION CHAMBER WITH 32 TELESCOPES MOUNTED
AT DIFFERENT ANGLES WERE USED. THE ENERGY SCALE WAS
CALIBRATED WITH RECOIL PROTONS AT 24 DEGREES FROM A
POLYETHYLENE FOIL, GIVING PROTONS OF ABOUT 12 MEV
ENERGY. IN ADDITION, 5 MEV ALPHA-PARTICLES FROM AN
AM-241 SOURCE WAS OBSERVED. IN TOTAL, THE ENERGY SCALE
WAS ESTABLISHED TO BETTER THAN 200 KEV. THE ANGULAR
RESOLUTION OF THE TELESCOPES WAS ON AVERAGE 13
ACTIVATION MONITOR. IN ADDITION, THE INTEGRAL NEUTRON
FLUX WAS DETERMINED WITH A LITHIUM-IODIDE
SCINTILLATION MONITOR. BOTH METHODS AGREED WITHIN 3
.THE SAMPLES WERE THICK COMPARED TO THE RANGE OF THE
MOST ENERGETIC (14.7 MEV) PROTONS. METALLIC SILVER AND
NIOBIUM SHEETS 0.7 MM THICK AND INDIUM SHEETS 1 MM
THICK WERE USED. FOR BACKGROUND DETERMINATION A THICK
GOLD TARGET REPLACED THE TARGET FOILS. THE SAMPLES
WERE IRRADIATED FOR ABOUT 100 HOURS WITH A MAXIMUM
